<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hello,</p>

<p>disabling the translator in Zend_Form_Element_Multi doesn't work as intended. If I disable translation, the Options are not added to the element!
Perhaps this bug has been introduced with this patch: <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3457">http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-3457</a></p>

<p>See here:</p>

<p>public function addMultiOption($option, $value = '')
.......
      if (!$this-&gt;_translateOption($option, $value)) {
            $this-&gt;options[$option] = $value;
        }
......</p>

<p>protected function _translateOption($option, $value)
{
        if ($this-&gt;translatorIsDisabled()) {
            return true;
        }
......</p>

<p>If I fix it (return false  if translator is disabled), it works again.</p>

